Title: Dynamic Interpretations of Constraint-Based Grammar Formalisms  
Author: Lawrence S. Moss David E. Johnson 
Keyword: Key words: Constraint-based formalism, evolving algebra  
Date: March 10, 1995  
Address: Bloomington, IN 47405 USA.  Yorktown Heights, NY 10598 USA.  
Affiliation: Mathematics and Computer Science Departments, Indiana University,  Mathematical Sciences Department, Thomas J. Watson Research Center, IBM Research Division,  
Abstract: We present a rendering of some common grammatical formalisms in terms of evolving algebras. Though our main concern in this paper is on constraint-based formalisms, we also discuss the more basic case of context-free grammars. Our aim throughout is to highlight the use of evolving algebras as a specification tool to obtain grammar formalisms. 
